Language name: BEJA
Language number: 4361
Alternate names: 
Classification: Afro-Asiatic, Cushitic
Comments: Vowels appear long and short.  Beja has what 
might be described as a pitch-accent system.

Sources: 

Hudson, R.A. 1974. A structural sketch of Beja.  African 
Language Studies 15:111-142.

Hudson, R.A. 1976. Beja. In M.L. Bender (ed.), The 
Non-Semitic Languages of Ethiopia. African Studies Center, 
Michigan State University, East Lansing: 97-132.